Senator Loitiptip, Sonko’s daughter Saumu hospitalised after bar fight             Cyrus Ombati  04th Jun 2019 15:30:59 GMT +0300 Cyrus Ombati  04th Jun 2019 15:30:59 GMT +0300 Cyrus Ombati   Lamu Senator Anwar Loitiptip was admitted to Aga Khan Hospital after sustaining injuries on Saturday night at Memphis Lounge in Kasarani, Nairobi. JHe was in the company of Saumu Mbuvui, the daughter of Nairobi Governor Mike Mbuvi Sonko when men set on him with clubs. [Standard]  Lamu Senator Anwar Loitiptip was admitted to Aga Khan Hospital after sustaining injuries on Saturday night at Memphis Lounge in Kasarani, Nairobi. JHe was in the company of Saumu Mbuvui, the daughter of Nairobi Governor Mike Mbuvi Sonko when men set on him with clubs. [Standard] Lamu Senator Anwar Loitiptip was admitted to Aga Khan Hospital after sustaining injuries on Saturday night at Memphis Lounge in Kasarani, Nairobi. JHe was in the company of Saumu Mbuvui, the daughter of Nairobi Governor Mike Mbuvi Sonko when men set on him with clubs. [Standard] Lamu Senator Anwar Loitiptip was admitted to Aga Khan Hospital after sustaining injuries on Saturday night at Memphis Lounge in Kasarani, Nairobi. JHe was in the company of Saumu Mbuvui, the daughter of Nairobi Governor Mike Mbuvi Sonko when men set on him with clubs.                     For the latest news in entertainment check out Sde.co.ke and Pulser.co.ke , for everything sports visit Gameyetu.co.ke and ladies we have you covered on Evewoman For the latest news in entertainment check out Sde.co.ke and Pulser.co.ke , for everything sports visit Gameyetu.co.ke and ladies we have you covered on Evewoman Sde.co.ke Pulser.co.ke Gameyetu.co.ke Evewoman Related Topics Lamu Senator Anwar Loitiptip Mike Sonko Agnes Saumu Mbuvi Bar fight